<TITLE> Fresh Iraq troop cuts hinge on security: Petraeus </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BAGHDAD,. Mon Jul 14,(bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The US military commander in Iraq said on Monday that security conditions would determine whether he makes recommendations for further troop withdrawals in the coming months. The comments by General David Petraeus came a day after The New York Times reported the Bush administration was already considering more troop cuts beginning in September. There are some 146,000 US soldiers in Iraq, down from a peak of 170,000 in 2007 when President George W Bush ordered five additional combat brigades to Iraq to try to drag the country back from the brink of civil war. The last of those extra brigades has already begun leaving Iraq and will have completed its withdrawal this month. "We are conducting a continuous assessment of the situation ... and should the conditions allow it, we will make additional recommendations, perhaps in the latter part of the summer, about additional reductions," Petraeus told a news conference
